President Obama spoke with President Erdogan of Turkey to express condolences for the recent terrorist attacks in Istanbul and the Turkish soldiers killed in Syria. They both agreed to stand united in the fight against terrorism. President Obama also thanked President Erdogan for Turkey's efforts in brokering a ceasefire in Aleppo and emphasized the need for a nationwide cessation of hostilities and a political solution to the conflict. They discussed the progress of the Coalition's campaign against ISIL in Iraq and Syria and stressed the importance of continued coordination between the US and Turkey. Finally, they highlighted the positive relationship they have had over the past eight years and their shared desire for strong relations between the two countries going forward.